RAFHA: Prince Faisal bin Khalid bin Sultan, governor of the Northern Borders, met on Saturday with directors from the government and service sectors at the Rafha governorate headquarters. He stressed the importance of following and meeting all planning standards compatible with the Kingdomâ€™s Vision 2030, and of coordiantion and cooperation between all agencies. In order to improve the level of services provided to citizens and reach objectives, all obstacles should be addressed, he added. Prince Faisal also urged the directors to continue to follow up on ongoing projects, facilitate their implementation and coordinate with contractors to resolve any outstanding issues. He praised the great efforts exerted by the Saudi government to provide all requirements for a decent standard of living for citizens and residents alike. During the meeting, he discussed the status of new projects being implemented in the governorate and reviewed the quality of services based on performance indicators. 